Clear the environment

rm(list = ls())

Load packages

Before loading the packages install them using install()

library(tidyverse)
library(summarytools)
library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)
library(readr)
library(vegan)
library(patchwork)
library(ggplot2)
library(gamm4)
library(pander)

Part 1: Importing and examining data

In this part the data frames were inspected in order to check the variable names and types. In some situations the data set was slightly modified for better further manipulation of them.

1a) Import data

Environmental <- read.csv("Data/Environmental_variables.csv")
Metadata <- read.csv("Data/Metadata_lat2018-2019.csv")
Herbivory <- read.csv("Data/Herbivory_latitudinal2018-2019.csv")
Benthic <- read.csv("Data/Percent_cover.csv")
Phlorotannins <- read.csv("Data/Phlorotannins.csv")
Predation <- read.csv("Data/Predation_latitudinal2018-2019.csv")
Size <- read.csv("Data/Size_estimations.csv")
Transects <- read.csv("Data/Transect2018-2019.csv")

1b) Inspect structure of data frames

  1. Site metadata
view(dfSummary(Metadata))

#Rename temperature variables to avoid confusion with replicate measures in Environmental data
Metadata <- rename(Metadata, Temperature_site = Temperature_C)
  1. Environmental data
view(dfSummary(Environmental))

Environmental <- Environmental %>%
  rename(D_oxygen_percent = X., D_oxygen_mgL = D_oxygen) %>% #Rename oxygen percent variable
  select(-Date,-Campaign,-Latitude) #Remove variables that are in Metadata
  1. Benthic cover
view(dfSummary(Benthic))
Benthic <- Benthic %>%
  select(-Date) #Remove variables that are in Metadata
  1. Herbivory
view(dfSummary(Herbivory))
Herbivory <- Herbivory %>%
  select(-Date,-Campaign,-Season) %>%# Remove variables that are in Metadata
  mutate(Consumed_proportion = (Initial_length_mm-Final_Length_mm)/Initial_length_mm)

For future analysis it was necessary to create major categories for Bait (squidpops vs crabs), and a category called Consumption which is 1 when Consumed_proportion is higher than 0 and 0 if Consumed_proportion is 0.

Herbivory <- mutate(Herbivory, Bait2 = case_when(Bait == "Lessonia_spicata" ~ "Lessonia sp.",
                                                 Bait == "Lessonia_berteroana" ~ "Lessonia sp."))
Herbivory <- mutate(Herbivory, Consumption = case_when(Consumed_proportion == 0 ~ 0,
                                              Consumed_proportion != 0 ~ 1))
  1. Predation
view(dfSummary(Predation))
Predation <- Predation %>%
  select(-Date,-Campaign,-Season)  %>%# Remove variables that are in Metadata
mutate(Consumed_proportion = (Initial_Individuals-Remaining_individuals)/Initial_Individuals, Consumed_individuals = Initial_Individuals-Remaining_individuals) #Add Consumed_proportion column

For future analysis it was necessary to create major categories for Bait (Squidpops vs Crabs) and Assay time (2 hours and 24 hours)

Predation <- mutate(Predation, Bait2 = case_when(Bait == "Squidpops" ~ "Squidpops",
                                                 Bait != "Squidpops" ~ "Crabs"), Assay_time2 = case_when(Assay_time == "24" ~ "24",
                                                 Bait != "24" ~ "2"))
  1. Phlorotannins
view(dfSummary(Phlorotannins))
Phlorotannins <- Phlorotannins %>%
  select(-Date,-Latitude) # Remove variables that are in metadata
  1. Size
view(dfSummary(Size))
Size <- Size %>%
  select(-Date,-Campaign) # Remove variables that are in Metadata
  1. Transects
view(dfSummary(Transects))
Transects <- Transects %>%
  select(-Date,-Campaign) # Remove variables that are in Metadata

Part 2: Manipulating datasets

In this section data sets are manipulated for future analysis. New data sets with means and combined with metadata and consumption are created.

2a) Environmental data

  1. Join Environmental data with metadata
Environmental_metadata <- Environmental %>%
    left_join(Metadata, by = "Site")
  1. Join Environmental data with consumption

First summarise environmental data per site

Environmental_2 <- Environmental_metadata %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude) %>%
  select(-D_oxygen_percent, -Conductivity_Ms, V_Visibility, -C_f, -C_i, -H_Visibility) #Keep only variables that will be used in the analysis

Environmental_sum_long <- Environmental_2 %>%
  gather(Env_Variable, Value, Temperature:RPM) %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude, Env_Variable)%>%
  summarise(Mean_value = mean(Value, na.rm=T),n = n(), sd = sd(Value,na.rm=T), se = sd/sqrt(n)) 

Environmental_sum <- Environmental_sum_long %>%
  select(Site, Env_Variable, Mean_value) %>%
pivot_wider(names_from = Env_Variable, values_from = Mean_value,
              values_fill = 0)

Then, add environmental data to consumption

  • Predation vs environmental data sets
Predation_env <- Predation %>%
    left_join(Environmental_sum, by = "Site")
  • Herbivory vs environmental data sets
Herbivory_env <- Herbivory %>%
  left_join(Environmental_sum, by = "Site")

2b): Benthic data

  1. Join benthic data with metadata
Benthic_metadata <- Benthic  %>%
    left_join(Metadata, by = "Site")
  1. Calculate mean, sd, and se by group
Benthic_mean <- Benthic_metadata %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude, Type)%>%
  summarise(Mean_cover = mean(Coverage),n = n(), sd = sd(Coverage), se = sd/sqrt(n))
  1. Join Environmental data with consumption

First, summarise benthic cover per site and change it to the wide format

Benthic_sum_wide <- Benthic %>%
  group_by(Site, Type) %>%
  summarise(cover_mean = mean(Coverage)) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = Type, values_from = cover_mean,
              values_fill = 0)
Benthic_sum_wide_var <- select(Benthic_sum_wide, Site, Kelp, Understorey_algae)

Then, add benthic data to consumption

  • Predation_env + Benthic summarised data
Predation_2 <- Predation_env %>%
    left_join(Benthic_sum_wide_var, by = "Site")
  • Herbivory_env + Benthic summarised data
Herbivory_2 <- Herbivory_env %>%
  left_join(Benthic_sum_wide_var, by = "Site")

2c): Fish length

  1. Join Size data with metadata
Size_metadata <- Size %>%
left_join(Metadata, by = c("Site"))
  1. Calculate mean, sd and se per group
Size_mean_sp<- Size_metadata %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude, Species, Type)%>%
  summarise(mean_Size_sp = mean(Size_cm))
Size_mean <- Size_mean_sp %>%
   group_by(Site, Latitude, Type)%>%
  summarise(mean_Size = mean(mean_Size_sp),n = n(), sd = sd(mean_Size_sp), se = sd/sqrt(n))
  1. Calculate mean of fish size and add it to consumption
Size_mean_wide <- Size_mean_sp %>%
  filter(Type == "Fish") %>%
  group_by(Site, Type)%>%
  summarise(mean_Size = mean(mean_Size_sp)) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = Type, values_from = mean_Size,
              values_fill = 0) %>%
  rename(Fish_size = Fish)

Then, add fish length data to consumption

  • Predation_env + fish size data
Predation_3 <- Predation_2 %>%
    left_join(Size_mean_wide, by = "Site")

2d) Species list (abundances and richness)

  1. Add metadata to Transects data set

Summary of species from transects. Prepare data to calculate abundances and species richness

#Join transects with metadata
Transect_metadata <- Transects %>%
left_join(Metadata, by = c("Site"))

Transect_sum <- Transect_metadata %>%
  filter(Method == "Transect") %>% #Select only data taken with visual transect method
  group_by(Site, Latitude, Census, Species) %>%
  summarise(Total_abundance = sum(Individuals))
  1. Calculate abundances
  • Calculate abundances by species

First, change data frame to the wide format

Transect_wide <- Transect_sum %>%
   ungroup()  %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = Species, values_from = Total_abundance,
              values_fill = 0)

Convert back to long format with Species and Abundance as columns. This will add rows with zeroes for all the species missing in each video

Transect_long <- Transect_wide %>%
  gather(Species, Abundance, Anisotremus_scapularis:Labrisomus_philippii)

#Obtain mean abundance per site and method
Transect_mean <- Transect_long %>%
      group_by(Site, Latitude, Species) %>%
     summarise(Mean_abundance = mean(Abundance),n = n(), sd = sd(Abundance), se = sd/sqrt(n))
  • Calculate abundances by group

Follow the same steps as abundances by type

TransectGroup_sum <- Transect_metadata %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude, Census, Group) %>%
  summarise(Total_abundance = sum(Individuals))

TransectGroup_wide <- TransectGroup_sum %>%
  ungroup()  %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = Group, values_from = Total_abundance,
              values_fill = 0)
TransectGroup_long <- TransectGroup_wide %>%
  gather(Group, Abundance, Herbivore_fish:Scavenger)

TransectGroup_mean <- TransectGroup_long %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude, Group) %>%
  summarise(Total_abundance = mean(Abundance),n = n(), sd = sd(Abundance), se = sd/sqrt(n))
  1. Calculate Species Richness

First, add a column of presence when abundance is higher than 0.

Transect_long <- Transect_long %>%
  mutate(Presence = if_else(Abundance > 0,1,0))

Calculate sum of all species in the same site and census.

Richness_transect <- Transect_long %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude, Census) %>%
  summarise(Richness = sum(Presence))

#Calculate mean by site  
Richness_mean <- Richness_transect %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude)%>%
  summarise(Mean_SR = mean(Richness),n = n(), sd = sd(Richness), se = sd/sqrt(n))
  1. Add abundances to consumption data

Calculate means and change it to the wide format

#Per species
Abundances_mean <- Transect_long%>%
  filter(Species == "Taliepus_sp.") %>%
  group_by(Site, Species)%>%
  summarise(Mean_Abundance = mean(Abundance)) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = Species, values_from = Mean_Abundance,
              values_fill = 0) %>%
  rename(Omnivorous_crab = Taliepus_sp.)

#Per Group
Group_abundances_mean <- TransectGroup_long%>%
  filter(Group == "Predatory_crab" | Group == "Predatory_fish"| Group == "Sea_star"| Group == "Herbivore_fish" | Group == "Herbivore_gastropod"| Group == "Urchin")%>%
  group_by(Site, Group)%>%
  summarise(Mean_Abundance = mean(Abundance)) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = Group, values_from = Mean_Abundance,
              values_fill = 0)

Then, add abundances data to consumption

  • Predation_env + group abundance summarised data
#Select only the needed columns
Group_abundances_mean_pred <- select(Group_abundances_mean, Site, Predatory_crab, Predatory_fish, Sea_star)

Predation_4 <- Predation_3 %>%
    left_join(Group_abundances_mean_pred, by = "Site")
  • Herbivory_env + Benthic summarised data
#Select only the needed columns
Group_abundances_mean_herb <- select(Group_abundances_mean, Site, Herbivore_fish, Urchin, Herbivore_gastropod)

Herbivory_3 <- Herbivory_2 %>%
  left_join(Group_abundances_mean_herb, by = "Site") %>%
  left_join(Abundances_mean, by = "Site")
  1. Add species richness to consumption data

Calculate means and change it to the wide format

Richness_meanpred <- Richness_transect %>%
  group_by(Site)%>%
  summarise(Mean_SR = mean(Richness))

Then, add abundances data to consumption

  • Predation_4 + species richness summarised data
Predation_5 <- Predation_4 %>%
    left_join(Richness_meanpred, by = "Site")
  • Herbivory_3 + species richness summarised data
Herbivory_4 <- Herbivory_3 %>%
  left_join(Richness_meanpred, by = "Site")

2e): Phlorotannins

  1. Add metadata
Phlorotannins_metadata <- Phlorotannins %>%
left_join(Metadata, by = c("Site"))
  1. Summarise phlorotannins per site
Phlorotannins_mean <- Phlorotannins_metadata %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude) %>%
  summarise(phloro_mean = mean(Phlorotannins), n = n(), sd = sd(Phlorotannins), se = sd/sqrt(n))
  1. Herbivory + phlorotannins
Phlorotannins_sum <- Phlorotannins %>%
  group_by(Site) %>%
  summarise(phloro_mean = mean(Phlorotannins))

Herbivory_phloro <- Herbivory %>%
  left_join(Phlorotannins_sum, by = "Site")

2f): Predation

Predation_sum <- Predation_5 %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude, Bait2, Assay_time2) %>%
  summarise(mean_consumption = mean(Consumed_proportion), n = n(), sd = sd(Consumed_proportion), se = sd/sqrt(n))

2g): Herbivory

Herbivory_sum <- Herbivory_4 %>%
  group_by(Site, Latitude, Bait2) %>%
  summarise(mean_consumption = mean(Consumed_proportion), n = n(), sd = sd(Consumed_proportion), se = sd/sqrt(n))

Part 3: Latitudinal patterns in explanatory variables

In this part we visually analysed latitudinal patterns in the explanatory variables chosen and then latitudinal patterns were analysed with simple regression

3a): Explore visual relationships

Set general theme for plots

Theme1 <- theme_bw() + 
    theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "white"),
          panel.grid.minor = element_line(colour = "white"), axis.text.y = element_text(size = 11), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 12), axis.text.x = element_text(size = 11), axis.title.x =     element_text(size = 12), plot.title=element_text(hjust=0.95, vjust=-8, size=10))

1) Environmental variables

  • Temperature vs latitude
Environmental_sum_long$Latitude <- Environmental_sum_long$Latitude*-1

Temperature_plot <- Environmental_sum_long %>% 
filter(Env_Variable == "Temperature") %>% 
ggplot(aes(x= Latitude, y=Mean_value)) + 
  geom_line() +
  geom_point()+
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=Mean_value-se, ymax=Mean_value+se), width=.2,
                 position=position_dodge(0.05)) + 
Theme1 +
labs( y="Temperature (°C)", x="Latitude") +
theme(axis.title.x=element_blank(),
        axis.text.x=element_blank(), axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 8))
  • Salinity vs latitude
Salinity_plot <- Environmental_sum_long %>% 
filter(Env_Variable == "Salinity_ppt") %>% 
ggplot(aes(x= Latitude, y=Mean_value)) + 
  geom_line() +
  geom_point()+
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=Mean_value-se, ymax=Mean_value+se), width=.2,
                 position=position_dodge(0.05)) + 
Theme1 +
labs( y="Salinity (ppt)", x="Latitude") +

        axis.text.x=element_blank(), axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 8))

6) Final plot

Temperature_plot + Salinity_plot + Oxygen_plot + Visibility_plot+ RPM_plot + Kelp_plot + Understorey_algae_plot + PredatoryFish_plot + HerbivorousFish_plot + PredatoryCrab_plot + OmnivorousCrab_plot + Sea_star_plot + Urchin_plot + HerbGastropod_plot + Richness_plot + Size_plot + plot_layout(ncol=4)

Figure S1: Latitudinal variation of explanatory variables. Environmental variables are temperature (°C), salinity (ppt), dissolved oxygen (mgL), visibility (m) water flow (RPM). Kelp cover and Understorey algae (UA) cover correspond to benthic cover (%). Predatory fish, herbivorous fish, predatory crab, omnivorous crab, sea stars, urchins and herbivorous gastropods are mean abundances (number of individuals). Species richness corresponds to the number of species and fish length (cm) is an estimated size. Error bars represent standard error

3b): Analyse relationships

The relationship of all explanatory variables was analysed using linear regressions.

  • Predation vs latitude
Predation_sum$Latitude <- Predation_sum$Latitude*-1

#Crabs 2h
Crabs2_plot <- Predation_sum%>%

ggplot(aes(x= Latitude, y=mean_consumption)) + 
  geom_line() +
  geom_point()+
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=mean_consumption-se, ymax=mean_consumption+se), width=.2,
                 position=position_dodge(0.05)) + 
Theme1 +
labs( y="Consumed proportion", x="Latitude") +
ggtitle("Crabs 2h")+ 
theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 11), axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.title.x =     element_blank(), plot.title=element_text(hjust=0.95, vjust=-8, size=10)) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1), breaks=seq(0, 1, 0.2))

4b): Analise relationships

  • Crabs 2h vs latitude

mutate(logMean = log(mean_consumption + 1))

summary(Crab2.lm)

## Call:
## lm(formula = logMean ~ Latitude, data = Crab2)

## -0.23717 -0.15619 -0.04944  0.10017  0.38032 
##

Part 5: Predation intensity: Effect of site-specific variables

First, create datasets to be used in the analysis

Predation_analysis <- Predation_5 %>%
  select(-Rope, -Bait, -Camera, -Assay_time, -Initial_Individuals, -Remaining_individuals, -Survival_proportion,-Consumed_proportion)

#Separate by Bait and Assay time 

Crabs_24 <- filter(Predation_analysis, Bait2 == "Crabs" & Assay_time2 == 24)
Crabs_2 <- filter(Predation_analysis, Bait2 == "Crabs" & Assay_time2 == 2)
Squidpops_24 <- filter(Predation_analysis, Bait2 == "Squidpops" & Assay_time2 == 24)
Squidpops_2 <- filter(Predation_analysis, Bait2 == "Squidpops" & Assay_time2 == 2)

5a): Standardize

#Crabs 24h
Crabs24_num <- Crabs_24 %>%
  select(-Site, -Bait2, -Assay_time2, -Consumed_individuals) 
Crabs24_stand <- decostand(Crabs24_num, method="range", na.rm = TRUE)
Crabs24_stand$Site <- Crabs_24$Site
Crabs24_stand$Consumed_individuals<- Crabs_24$Consumed_individuals
#Crabs 2h 
Crabs2_num <- Crabs_2 %>%
  select(-Site, -Bait2, -Assay_time2, -Consumed_individuals) 
Crabs2_stand <- decostand(Crabs2_num, method="range", na.rm = TRUE)
Crabs2_stand$Site <- Crabs_2$Site
Crabs2_stand$Consumed_individuals<- Crabs_2$Consumed_individuals
#Squidpops 24h
Squidpops24_num <- Squidpops_24 %>%
  select(-Site, -Bait2, -Assay_time2, -Consumed_individuals) 
Squidpops24_stand <- decostand(Squidpops24_num, method="range", na.rm = TRUE)
Squidpops24_stand$Site <- Squidpops_24$Site
Squidpops24_stand$Consumed_individuals<- Squidpops_24$Consumed_individuals
#Squidpops 2h
Squidpops2_num <- Squidpops_2 %>%
  select(-Site, -Bait2, -Assay_time2, -Consumed_individuals) 
Squidpops2_stand <- decostand(Squidpops2_num, method="range", na.rm = TRUE)
Squidpops2_stand$Site <- Squidpops_2$Site
Squidpops2_stand$Consumed_individuals<- Squidpops_2$Consumed_individuals

5b) Model selection: Crabs 2h

This code was supplied by Dr. Joel Williams.

1) Model selection loop

## step 1 mode selection loop
m1s <- list()
for(i in c("Temperature", "D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Predatory_crab", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ ",i, ",data = Crabs2_stand, random =~(1|Site), family = poisson)") # The model formula with random factors and distribution etc. i represent each individual variable from the list above
  m1s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Temperature  D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Predatory_crab  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
# This loop prints the summary(m1) for every model into a text file. Could be handy for writing the paper
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m1s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m1s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m1s[[i]]$gam))
}

# This line will list in order the AIC for each model. Select the variable with the lowest AIC and place it in the model formula in Step 2.
sort(sapply(m1s,function(x) AIC(x$mer)))
##       Temperature      D_oxygen_mgL              Kelp      Salinity_ppt 
##          420.0849          422.3158          424.1537          424.3317 
##           Mean_SR          Sea_star    Predatory_crab    Predatory_fish 
##          424.9734          425.3614          426.1651          426.6511 
##         Fish_size Understorey_algae               RPM      V_Visibility 
##          426.7192          426.8924          427.0288          427.0557

2) Start with the first variable (the lowest AIC)

m2s <- list()
cov <- c("D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Predatory_crab", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~  Temperature + ",i, ",data = Crabs2_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m2s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Predatory_crab  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m2s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$gam))
}

3) Start with temperature and visibility (two variables that best explain)

m3s <- list()
cov <- c("D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Predatory_crab", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ Temperature + V_Visibility + ",i, ",data = Crabs2_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m3s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Predatory_crab  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp3.txt")
for(i in names(m3s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$gam))
}

4) Start with temperature, visibility and predatory crab

m3s <- list()
cov <- c("D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ Temperature + V_Visibility + Predatory_crab + ",i, ",data = Crabs2_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m3s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp3.txt")
for(i in names(m3s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$gam))
}

##          419.9454

5) Start with temperature, visibility, predatory crab and understorey algae

m3s <- list()
cov <- c("D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "Kelp", "Mean_SR", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ Temperature + V_Visibility + Predatory_crab + Understorey_algae + ",i, ",data = Crabs2_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m3s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  Kelp  Mean_SR  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp3.txt")
for(i in names(m3s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$gam))
}

Temperature is the variable that best explain the variation. Visibility, abundances of predatory crab and understorey algae cover are part of the final model. There is a significant relationship between crabs consumption temperature, visibility and abundance of predatory crabs.

7) Plotting prediction

  • Temperature

  • Visibility

  • Predatory Crabs

5c) Model selection: Crabs 24

1) Model selection loop

m1s <- list()
for(i in c("Temperature", "D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Predatory_crab", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ ",i, ",data = Crabs24_stand, random =~(1|Site), family = poisson)") 
  
  m1s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Temperature  D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Predatory_crab  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m1s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m1s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m1s[[i]]$gam))
}

2) Starting with the first variable (the lowest AIC)

m2s <- list()
cov <- c("D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Predatory_crab", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ Temperature + ",i, ",data = Crabs24_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m2s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Predatory_crab  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m2s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$gam))
}

3) Starting with temperature and salinity (two variables that best explain)

m3s <- list()
cov <- c("D_oxygen_mgL","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Predatory_crab", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ Temperature + Salinity_ppt + ",i, ",data = Crabs24_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m3s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## D_oxygen_mgL  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Predatory_crab  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp3.txt")
for(i in names(m3s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$gam))
}

1) Model selection loop

m1s <- list()
for(i in c("Temperature", "D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Predatory_crab", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ ",i, ",data = Squidpops2_stand, random =~(1|Site), family = poisson)") 
  m1s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Temperature  D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Predatory_crab  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m1s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m1s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m1s[[i]]$gam))
}

2) Starting with the first variable (the lowest AIC)

m2s <- list()
cov <- c("Temperature", "D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ Predatory_crab + ",i, ",data = Squidpops2_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m2s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Temperature  D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m2s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$gam))
}

3) Starting with predatory crab and fish size

m2s <- list()
cov <- c("Temperature", "D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ Predatory_crab + Fish_size + ",i, ",data = Squidpops2_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m2s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Temperature  D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Sea_star  Predatory_fish
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m2s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$gam))
}

4) Starting with predatory crab, fish size and temperature

m2s <- list()
cov <- c("D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ Predatory_crab + Fish_size + Temperature + ",i, ",data = Squidpops2_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m2s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Sea_star  Predatory_fish
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m2s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$gam))
}

5) Starting with predatory crab, fish size, temperature and dissolved oxygen

m2s <- list()
cov <- c("Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ Predatory_crab + Fish_size + Temperature + D_oxygen_mgL + ",i, ",data = Squidpops2_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m2s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Sea_star  Predatory_fish
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m2s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$gam))
}

6) Starting with predatory crab, fish size, temperature, dissolved oxygen and kelp cover

m2s <- list()
cov <- c("Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ Predatory_crab + Fish_size + Temperature + D_oxygen_mgL + Kelp + ",i, ",data = Squidpops2_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m2s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Sea_star  Predatory_fish
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m2s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$gam))
}

5f) Model selection: Squidpops 24h

1) Model selection loop

m1s <- list()
for(i in c("Temperature", "D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Predatory_crab", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~ ",i, ",data = Squidpops24_stand, random =~(1|Site), family = poisson)") 
  m1s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Temperature  D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Predatory_crab  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m1s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m1s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m1s[[i]]$gam))
}

##       Temperature      Salinity_ppt              Kelp          Sea_star 
##          445.4266          449.4612          452.6577          453.1484 
##         Fish_size    Predatory_fish      V_Visibility               RPM

2) Start with the first variable (the lowest AIC)

m2s <- list()
cov <- c("D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Predatory_crab", "Sea_star", "Predatory_fish","Fish_size")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumed_individuals ~  Temperature + ",i, ",data = Squidpops24_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = poisson)")
  m2s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Predatory_crab  Sea_star  Predatory_fish  Fish_size
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m2s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$gam))
}

Part 6: Herbivory intensity: Effect of site specific variables

First, create datasets to be used in the analysis

Herbivory_analysis <- Herbivory_4 %>%
  select(-Rope, -Bait, -Camera, -Hours, -Initial_length_mm, -Final_Length_mm, -Scraped, -Survival_proportion,-Consumed_proportion)

1) Standardize

Herb_all_num <- Herbivory_analysis %>%
  select(-Site, -Consumption, -Bait2) 
Herb_all_stand <- decostand(Herb_all_num, method="range")
Herb_all_stand$Site <- Herbivory_analysis$Site
Herb_all_stand$Consumption<- Herbivory_analysis$Consumption

6a) Model selection

1) Model selection loop

m1s <- list()
for(i in c("Temperature", "D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Understorey_algae", "Mean_SR", "Herbivore_fish", "Urchin", "Omnivorous_crab", "Herbivore_gastropod")) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumption ~ ",i, ",data = Herb_all_stand, random =~(1|Site), family = binomial)")
  m1s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Temperature  D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Understorey_algae  Mean_SR  Herbivore_fish  Urchin  Omnivorous_crab  Herbivore_gastropod
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m1s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m1s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m1s[[i]]$gam))
}

##   Understorey_algae     Omnivorous_crab        Salinity_ppt              Urchin 
##            470.8265            472.1534            473.3369            476.3294 
##        D_oxygen_mgL         Temperature                Kelp             Mean_SR 
##            476.6002            477.0763            477.2913            477.4219

2) Starting with the first variable (the lowest AIC)

m2s <- list()
cov <- c("Temperature", "D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Mean_SR", "Herbivore_fish", "Urchin", "Omnivorous_crab", "Herbivore_gastropod")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumption  ~ Understorey_algae + ",i, ",data = Herb_all_stand, random =~(1|Site), family = binomial)")
  m2s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Temperature  D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Mean_SR  Herbivore_fish  Urchin  Omnivorous_crab  Herbivore_gastropod
sink("temp.txt")
for(i in names(m2s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m2s[[i]]$gam))
}

3) Starting with understorey algae and omnivorous crabs (two variables that best explain)

m3s <- list()
cov <- c("Temperature", "D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Mean_SR", "Herbivore_fish", "Urchin", "Herbivore_gastropod")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumption ~ Understorey_algae + Omnivorous_crab + ",i, ",data = Herb_all_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = binomial)")
  m3s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Temperature  D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Mean_SR  Herbivore_fish  Urchin  Herbivore_gastropod
sink("temp3.txt")
for(i in names(m3s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$gam))
}

4) Starting with understorey algae, omnivorous crabs and herbivorous gastropods

m3s <- list()
cov <- c("Temperature", "D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Mean_SR", "Herbivore_fish", "Urchin")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumption ~ Understorey_algae + Omnivorous_crab + Herbivore_gastropod + ",i, ",data = Herb_all_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = binomial)")
  m3s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## Temperature  D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Mean_SR  Herbivore_fish  Urchin
sink("temp3.txt")
for(i in names(m3s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$gam))
}

5) Starting with understorey algae, omnivorous crabs, herbivorous gastropods and temperature

m3s <- list()
cov <- c("D_oxygen_mgL","Salinity_ppt","RPM", "V_Visibility", "Kelp", "Mean_SR", "Herbivore_fish", "Urchin")
for(i in cov) {
  cat(i," ")
  cmd <- paste("gamm4(Consumption ~ Understorey_algae + Omnivorous_crab + Herbivore_gastropod + Temperature + ",i, ",data = Herb_all_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = binomial)")
  m3s[[i]] <- eval(parse(text=cmd))
}
## D_oxygen_mgL  Salinity_ppt  RPM  V_Visibility  Kelp  Mean_SR  Herbivore_fish  Urchin
sink("temp3.txt")
for(i in names(m3s)) {
  cat("\n *****",i,"****\n\n")
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$mer))
  print(summary(m3s[[i]]$gam))
}

5) Check final model

finalmodel_herbivory <- gamm4(Consumption ~ Understorey_algae + Omnivorous_crab + Herbivore_gastropod + Temperature, data = Herb_all_stand, random =~(1|Site) , family = binomial)

Part 7: Figures of model selection results

7a): Crabs 2h

1) Temperature prediction

library("mgcv")
newdata_C2 <- data.frame(
  Temperature = rep(seq(from = min(Crabs2_stand$Temperature), to = max(Crabs2_stand$Temperature), length.out = 100), 5), V_Visibility = 0, Predatory_crab = 0, Understorey_algae = 0)
newdata_C2 <- cbind(newdata_C2, predict(finalmodel_Crabs2$gam, newdata_C2 , type = "link", se.fit=TRUE))
newdata_C2 <- within(newdata_C2, {
  Consumed_individuals <- exp(fit)
  LL <- exp(fit - 1.96 * se.fit)
  UL <- exp(fit + 1.96 * se.fit)
})
ggplot(newdata_C2, aes(Temperature, Consumed_individuals)) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = LL, ymax = UL), alpha = .25) +
  geom_line(size = 1) +
  labs(x = "Temperature", y = "Predicted n° of Consumed Individuals")  + Theme1 +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 1, 0.2)) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,5.8), breaks = seq(0, 5, 1))

Save the plot in tiff format

ggsave("TC2.tiff", units="mm", width=140, height=100, dpi=300, compression = 'lzw')

model_phloro <- gamm4(Consumption ~ phloro_mean, data = Herbivory_phloro, random =~(1|Site) , family = binomial)
